mxCell.value: Departamento

• Department

    • Attributes:
      • dept_code (PK)
      • name
    • Relationships:
      • A department can have multiple professors.

  • Professor

    • Attributes:
      • professor_id (PK)
      • name
      • hiring_date
      • dept_code (FK → Department.dept_code)
    • Relationships:
      • Each professor belongs to a single department.
      • A professor can teach several courses.

  • Course

    • Attributes:
      • course_code (PK)
      • name
      • description
      • professor_id (FK → Professor.professor_id)
      • schedule
    • Relationships:
      • Each course is taught by one professor.
      • Courses may have prerequisites (modeled in a separate table).

  • Prerequisite

    • Attributes:
      • course_code (FK → Course.course_code)
      • prerequisite_code (FK → Course.course_code)
    • Relationships:
      • This table registers that for enrollment in a course (course_code), the student must have completed another course (prerequisite_code).

  • Student

    • Attributes:
      • student_id (PK)
      • name
      • birth_date
    • Relationships:
      • A student can enroll in multiple courses (modeled via a many-to-many relationship through the Enrollment table).
      • A student can take various evaluations for the courses in which they are enrolled.

  • Enrollment

    • Attributes:
      • student_id (FK → Student.student_id)
      • course_code (FK → Course.course_code)
      • enrollment_date
      • final_grade
    • Relationships:
      • This table records the enrollment of a student in a course, handling the many-to-many relationship between Student and Course.

  • Evaluation

    • Attributes:
      • evaluation_id (PK)
      • evaluation_date
      • course_code (FK → Course.course_code)
    • Relationships:
      • A course can have several evaluations (e.g., exams, projects).

  • Evaluation_Student

    • Attributes:
      • student_id (FK → Student.student_id)
      • evaluation_id (FK → Evaluation.evaluation_id)
      • grade
    • Relationships:
      • This table records the grade that a student obtains on a given evaluation, modeling the many-to-many relationship between Student and Evaluation.
